>> title: Smoky Black Beans
>> cuisine: Mexican
>> tags: protein, vegan, gluten-free, soy-free
>> servings: 8
>> yield: 4 cups
>> storage_days: 5
>> storage_method: refrigerated
>> reheat: Microwave or saucepan with splash of water.

Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in #large pot{} over medium heat.

Add @yellow onion{1}(diced) and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}.

Add @garlic{4%cloves}(minced) and @jalapeño{1}(seeded and minced), cook ~{1%minute}.

Add @ground cumin{2%tsp}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @chili powder{1%tsp}, and @dried oregano{1/2%tsp}. Stir ~{30%seconds}.

Add @black beans{3%cans}(15 oz each, drained and rinsed, reserve 1/2 cup liquid), @chipotle pepper in adobo{1}(minced), @adobo sauce{1%tbsp}, and @reserved bean liquid{1/2%cup}. Stir well.

Simmer ~{10-15%minutes}, stirring occasionally, until thickened.

Mash about 1/4 of the beans with back of #spoon{} for creamier texture.

Stir in @fresh lime juice{2%tbsp} and @kosher salt{1/2%tsp}. Taste and adjust.

Cool and store. Add @fresh cilantro{} when serving.

-- Used in: Tacos, burrito bowls, stuffed sweet potatoes, taco salad
